com.googlecode.aluminumproject.annotations

Annotation Type Injected


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface Injected
    Used to indicate that a field in an action, action contribution, function, or converter is expected to be injected by its factory.

    Which field types are allowed to be annotated depends on the type of the target object. Each of them should be able to obtain the current configuration. Objects that are created by library elements (i.e. actions, action contributions, and functions) should also be able to get a hold of their factories.
